main event: A civilian in Indianapolis, Indiana observed two connected objects that appeared to be two soup bowls, described as having conflicting data regarding their appearance and movement.
interesting points: The object was observed for up to 50 seconds, with one witness stating the sighting lasted only a few seconds., The objects were observed moving in a westerly direction resembling a meteor with three satellite debris creating a contrail., The report noted a lack of physical evidence and the conclusion was marked as conflicting data., Several witnesses reported seeing the objects under different durations and conditions, indicating varying perceptions., The report mentions that the objects were assessed as larger than a dime at arm's length and might have been influenced by surrounding weather conditions.
sighted object: two connected circular objects resembling soup bowls
witness description: A civilian observer who reported the sighting.
